You are thinking in the right direction. Let's clear the exact rule of covariant return type.

In method overriding:

Parent method return type = Parent class type
Child overridden method return type can be:
Same type ✅
Child class type (subclass of parent return type) ✅

But not any random type ❌

Example:

class Animal {

    Animal print() {
        return new Animal();
    }
}


class Dog extends Animal {

    // Same return type
    Animal print() {
        return new Animal();
    }
}

Valid.

Now covariant:

class Animal {

    Animal print() {
        return new Animal();
    }
}


class Dog extends Animal {

    // Dog is child of Animal
    Dog print() {
        return new Dog();
    }
}

Also valid ✅

Because:

Dog IS-A Animal

So Java allows narrowing the return type.

